messages.message:
Some additional feedback about project copy functionality (I mentioned a couple here (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C0516UPPMT3/p1729111533611009))

1. When we copy a build project, can we show the edited document names instead of the original document names? Users spend time renaming documents in the projects and they go away when you copy
2. I've seen more extraction failures in copied projects. These screenshots show them, and I've seen it in other projects too. Is there a reason for that?
On #2, extraction seems to work again after individual manual retries, but the initial extraction failures are not encouraging as a user

cc: @Sayd do you have thoughts here? I think showing the edited name makes sense but I don't know how we actually store it

The second one feels like a bug. Lets see what @Sayd thinks!
This makes sense. I have a ticket for addresssing the first and it will actually cover the second point as well (will try copy the results of extraction with the documents)
@Sayd would you be able to share the ticket?
@Sayd Can you give me a brief explanation of why these failures happen and how that fix will help?
@david.lee can you share the project. I will take a look into the specifics of this case
@Sayd https://aihub.instabase.com/build/0192afa1-e3e4-7b20-8a35-1415628e7cd0 FYI It works now but initially it returned more failures
